    {
        "content": "<p>According to this doc above, I created a link to ld.lld and this error stopped (resolved)... but when I try to run the <em>rusttest</em>, <em>rust-analyzer</em> commands I'm still getting an error: <strong>No rule to process target</strong></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rusttest</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">CALL</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">checksyscalls</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">sh</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">DESCEND</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">objtool</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">INSTALL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libsubcmd_headers</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">DESCEND</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bpf</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">resolve_btfids</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">INSTALL</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">libsubcmd_headers</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">process</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">rusttest</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">Stop</span><span class=\"p\">.</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>my .config</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">grep</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CONFIG_RUST</span>\n<span class=\"n\">CONFIG_RUSTC_VERSION</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">108100</span>\n<span class=\"n\">CONFIG_RUST_IS_AVAILABLE</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">y</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is there still a parameter or file missing? What would this rule be?</p>",
