    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm... I still can't reproduce it, and I have matched the environment and config fairly close. The error is quite weird, though, e.g. it could happen if there is a character removed at the end of the command. Sorry for asking this, but just to double-check, is your tree clean, i.e. no Git diff w.r.t. v6.15-rc1?</p>\n<p>By the way, I don't think you were calling with just <code>make LLVM=1</code>, at least in the first message above, but it should not matter. Similarly, that Clang 21 should not matter, but it is uncommon to see -- I don't see it even on pluky. Out of curiosity, where did you get LLVM from?</p>\n<p>Could you perhaps try to reproduce it in a clean setup/environment, e.g. in a container or similar?</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 511948057,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1744582941
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe I found the reason.I create another archlinux VM，and It work well with the config.The make version of Arch is GNU Make 4.4.1 while my development server  is GNU Make 4.2.1 .After update the make version ,I work well on it too.But I'm still puzzled as to why this script has a make version restriction, I didn't notice this in the documentation.</p>",
